comments: Ayton (PHX) and Finney-Smith (DAL) mutually engage in marginal contact prior to disengaging off ball.
Wood (DAL) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with the side of Lee's (PHX) foot after he returns to the floor.
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Bullock (DAL) establishes himself in Bridges? (PHX) path and collapses his forearm in to absorb the marginal contact during the pick.

Payne (PHX) avoids making contact with Doncic's (DAL) arm at the end of his drive. Booker's (PHX) arms are in a vertical position when Doncic extends his arms towards Booker and incidental contact occurs during the pass.
Payne (PHX) establishes himself in Finney-Smith?s (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
During the rebound, Lee (PHX) makes contact with the ball and deflects it away from Kleber (DAL) prior to the incidental contact to Kleber's shoulder on his follow-through.
Bridges (PHX) momentarily places his hands on Finney-Smith's (DAL) back and marginal contact occurs as he releases away on his cut toward the basket.
During the rebound, Doncic (DAL) makes clean hand on ball contact to tip the loose ball away from Bridges (PHX).
Finney-Smith (DAL) and Ayton (PHX) both have their feet planted on the ground as they pursue the loose ball and any foot to ball contact is deemed incidental.
Wood (DAL) secures the loose ball and Dallas is granted a timeout prior to Bridges (PHX) tying the ball up for a jump ball.
Bullock (DAL) firms up in Bridges? (PHX) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the switch on the pick.
Lee (PHX) jumps into Doncic (DAL) and initiates contact with his body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in Finney-Smith?s (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.

Dinwiddie (DAL) moves alongside of Lee (PHX) with one forearm collapsed against his body and the other arm in a vertical position. Marginal contact occurs when he removes his arm from Lee's side at the end of the drive.
Dinwiddie (DAL) legally contests Lee?s (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Dinwiddie (DAL) and Bridges (PHX) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs as the ball is brought up the court.
Dinwiddie (DAL) slightly extends his arms and marginal contact occurs with Bridges (PHX) as he releases toward the perimeter.
Lee (PHX) legally contests Doncic?s (DAL) jump shot attempt.
